# Day 05 - IP Address Analysis

## Objective
Learn how IP addresses identify devices on a network and analyze IPv4 packets using Wireshark.

## What I Learned

- Difference between Public and Private IP addresses.
- Source IP identifies the sender.
- Destination IP identifies the receiver.
- IPv4 packets contain addressing information.
- TTL (Time To Live) limits how many routers a packet can traverse.
- Security analysts inspect Source IPs to identify where network traffic originates.

## Practical

- Opened Wireshark.
- Applied the `ip` display filter.
- Inspected IPv4 packet details.
- Identified Source and Destination IP addresses.
- Observed the TTL field.

## Reflection

Today I learned how devices communicate using IP addresses and how to identify the sender and receiver of network traffic in Wireshark.
